com.acrolinx.javasdk.api.report

Enum FlagType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<FlagType>
      • com.acrolinx.javasdk.api.report.FlagType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<FlagType>

    public enum FlagType
extends Enum<FlagType>
    The type of a Flag. The FlagType describes the type of issue a flag represents in the text. In the CheckSettings you can enable and disable the related checking modules.

    If you're going to match a flag type to a color code, your code may look like this:

    FlagType flagType = flag.getType();
    if (flagType == FlagType.GRAMMAR) {
    //FT_GRAMMAR color
    } else if (flagType == FlagType.STYLE) {
    //FT_STYLE color
    } else if (flagType == FlagType.REUSE) {
    //FT_REUSE color
    } else if (flagType == FlagType.TERMCANDIDATE) {
    //FT_NEW_TERM color
    } else if(flagType == FlagType.SPELLING) {
    if(flag.getSuggestions() == null || flag.getSuggestions().isEmpty()) {
    //UNKNOWN word color (but we'll probably render it with
    FT_SPELLING_ERROR, too many colors)
    } else {
    //FT_SPELLING_ERROR color
    }
    }
    else if (flagType == FlagType.TERM) {
    if(flag instanceof TermFlag) {
    TermStatus status = ((TermFlag)flag).getTermStatus();
    if(status == TermStatus.DEPRECATED) {
    //FT_ILLEGAL_TERM color
    } else if(status == TermStatus.ADMITTED) {
    //FT_ADMITTED color
    } else if(status == TermStatus.VALID) {
    //FT_LEGAL_TERM color
    }
    }
    }

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      EXTRACTION
      The EXTRACTION is used to display extraction settings as markings in the text.
      GRAMMAR
      The GRAMMAR indicates that there was a grammar issue in the text.
      REUSE
      The REUSE indicates that there was a Reuse match for one sentence in the checked text.
      SEO
      The SEO is used to display SEO flags.
      SPELLING
      The SPELLING indicates that there was a spelling issue in the text.
      STYLE
      The STYLE indicates that there was a style issue in the text.
      TERM
      The TERM indicates that a term from the Acrolinx Server terminology database was found in the text.
      TERMCANDIDATE
      The TERMCANDIDATE indicates that the Acrolinx Server found a term candidate in the checked text.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • SPELLING

        public static final FlagType SPELLING
        The SPELLING indicates that there was a spelling issue in the text. For example a misspelled or duplicate word. See also SpellingFlag.

      • GRAMMAR

        public static final FlagType GRAMMAR
        The GRAMMAR indicates that there was a grammar issue in the text. For example a wrong comma or case.

      • STYLE

        public static final FlagType STYLE
        The STYLE indicates that there was a style issue in the text. For example a use of passive form or unnecessary words.

      • TERM

        public static final FlagType TERM
        The TERM indicates that a term from the Acrolinx Server terminology database was found in the text. A TermFlag has a TermStatus to indicate if it is matching a depreciated, admitted or a valid term in the text.

      • TERMCANDIDATE

        public static final FlagType TERMCANDIDATE
        The TERMCANDIDATE indicates that the Acrolinx Server found a term candidate in the checked text. Please note that a user needs a privilege to see new terms. If this privilege is missing (which is default) the new terms flags are filtered by the API.

      • REUSE

        public static final FlagType REUSE
        The REUSE indicates that there was a Reuse match for one sentence in the checked text.

      • EXTRACTION

        public static final FlagType EXTRACTION
        The EXTRACTION is used to display extraction settings as markings in the text.

      • SEO

        public static final FlagType SEO
        The SEO is used to display SEO flags.
